# Dry-Run Prompts for GitHub Copilot Chat

Copy-paste any of these prompts into GitHub Copilot Chat (in VS Code) to perform
a dry-run remediation. Copilot will read the `.github/copilot-instructions.md`
automatically.

---

## Prompt 1: Dry Run - Single Service (Full Remediation)

```
@workspace DRY RUN: Apply FULL Snyk remediation to the PartyAuth pom.xml.

This must include ALL of the following:
1. JDK upgrade: java.version, maven.compiler.source, maven.compiler.target → 21
2. Compiler plugin: <source> and <target> → 21
3. Add CVE remediation properties (spring-framework.version, spring-retry.version, micrometer.version, netty.version, tomcat.version)
4. Remove version mismatches (spring-boot-starter-webmvc-test has 4.0.6 — remove it)
5. Update outdated direct dependencies (commons-io 2.21.0 → 2.22.0)

DO NOT modify any files. Show me:
- The complete BEFORE and AFTER XML diff for <properties> section
- The BEFORE and AFTER for maven-compiler-plugin
- Any dependency version tags to remove
- The mvn commands I should run to validate
```

---

## Prompt 2: Dry Run - All Services

```
@workspace DRY RUN: Apply FULL Snyk remediation across ALL 6 microservice pom.xml files.

For EACH service, show:
1. JDK upgrade: 17 → 21 (all 5 locations)
2. CVE properties to add (spring-framework, spring-retry, micrometer, netty, tomcat)
3. Version mismatches to fix (spring-boot-starter-webmvc-test, spring-boot-starter-aop)
4. Direct dependencies to update (commons-io, json, spring-kafka, mockito)
5. Risk level (low/medium/high)

DO NOT modify any files. Output as a structured report per service.
```

---

## Prompt 3: Dry Run - Specific CVE

```
@workspace DRY RUN: Remediate CVE-2026-41851 (spring-core vulnerability, needs 6.2.19) across all 6 services.

Show the exact <properties> change needed for each pom.xml.
Also include the JDK 17→21 upgrade since it is part of the same remediation cycle.
Identify which services already have the fix and which need it.
DO NOT modify files.
```

---

## Prompt 4: Apply - Single Service

```
@workspace Apply FULL Snyk remediation to PartyAuth pom.xml. This includes:

1. Change java.version, maven.compiler.source, maven.compiler.target from 17 to 21
2. Change maven-compiler-plugin <source> and <target> from 17 to 21
3. Add these properties after the java version properties:
   - spring-framework.version = 6.2.19
   - spring-retry.version = 2.0.13
   - micrometer.version = 1.15.12
   - netty.version = 4.1.135.Final
   - tomcat.version = 10.1.55
4. Remove <version>4.0.6</version> from spring-boot-starter-webmvc-test
5. Update commons-io from 2.21.0 to 2.22.0

Apply all changes to the pom.xml file.
```

---

## Prompt 5: Apply - All Services at Once

```
@workspace Apply FULL Snyk remediation to ALL 6 microservice pom.xml files.

For every service:
1. Upgrade JDK 17 → 21 (properties + compiler plugin)
2. Add CVE remediation properties (spring-framework.version=6.2.19, spring-retry.version=2.0.13, micrometer.version=1.15.12, netty.version=4.1.135.Final, tomcat.version=10.1.55)
3. Remove explicit versions on spring-boot-starter-webmvc-test and spring-boot-starter-aop
4. Update commons-io to 2.22.0, org.json:json to 20240303 where outdated

Apply changes to all pom.xml files.
```

---

## Prompt 6: Validate After Applying

```
@workspace I've applied Snyk remediation to PartyAuth pom.xml. What mvn commands should I run to verify:
1. JDK 21 is correctly set
2. Spring Framework resolves to 6.2.19
3. No Boot 4.x version mismatches remain
4. Build compiles successfully

Show me the commands and expected output for each.
```

---

## Setup Checklist

Before running these prompts, ensure:

1. [ ] Open the workspace containing all 6 service repos in VS Code
2. [ ] Place `.github/copilot-instructions.md` at the workspace root
3. [ ] Have GitHub Copilot Chat extension installed and active
4. [ ] Use `@workspace` prefix so Copilot reads the full workspace context

## Tips

- Start with Prompt 1 on PartyAuth (simplest service with a known mismatch)
- Verify Copilot shows `<java.version>21</java.version>` in the AFTER block
- If Copilot misses the JDK upgrade, add "Remember: JDK 17→21 is mandatory" to the prompt
- Once dry-run looks correct, use Prompt 4 to apply to one service
- Run `.\validate-remediation.ps1 -ProjectDir <path>` after applying
- Then use Prompt 5 to apply to all remaining services
